[onDidSaveTextDocument]: file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/fzf-recent-dirs.fish
onDefinition
function fzf-recent-dirs
    get_recent_dirs | __fzf_helper_cmd
end


function __fzf_helper_cmd
    set -l preview_cmd 'exa -F --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore {}'
    fzf --tiebreak=index --preview "$preview_cmd" --preview-window=right:60%:wrap "$_FZF_NAV_KEYS" 
end

      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-complete -d 'fzf completion and print selection back to commandline'\n\t# As of 2.6, fish's \"complete\" function does not understand\n\t# subcommands. Instead, we use the same hack as __fish_complete_subcommand and\n\t# extract the subcommand manually.\n\tset -l cmd (commandline -co) (commandline -ct)\n\tswitch $cmd[1]\n\t\tcase env sudo\n\t\t\tfor i in (seq 2 (count $cmd))\n\t\t\t\tswitch $cmd[$i]\n\t\t\t\t\tcase '-*'\n\t\t\t\t\tcase '*=*'\n\t\t\t\t\tcase '*'\n\t\t\t\t\t\tset cmd $cmd[$i..-1]\n\t\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\tend\n\tend\n        set cmd (string join -- ' ' $cmd)\n\n\tset -l complist (complete -C$cmd)\n\tset -l result\n        #string join -- \\n $complist | sort | eval (__fzfcmd) -m --select-1 --exit-0 --header '(commandline)' | cut -f1 | while read -l r; set result $result $r; end\n        string join -- \\n $complist | sort | fzf -m --select-1 --exit-0 --header '(commandline)' | cut -f1 | while read -l r; set result $result $r; end \n\tset prefix (string sub -s 1 -l 1 -- (commandline -t))\n\tfor i in (seq (count $result))\n\t\tset -l r $result[$i]\n\t\tswitch $prefix\n\t\t\tcase \"'\"\n\t\t\t\tcommandline -t -- (string escape -- $r)\n\t\t\tcase '\"'\n\t\t\t\tif string match '*\"*' -- $r >/dev/null\n\t\t\t\t\tcommandline -t --  (string escape -- $r)\n\t\t\t\telse\n\t\t\t\t\tcommandline -t -- '\"'$r'\"'\n\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\tcase '~'\n\t\t\t\tcommandline -t -- (string sub -s 2 (string escape -n -- $r))\n\t\t\tcase '*'\n\t\t\t\tcommandline -t -- (string escape -n -- $r)\n\t\tend\n\t\t[ $i -lt (count $result) ]; and commandline -i ' '\n\tend\n\n\tcommandline -f repaint\nend\n"
    }
  }
}

    }
  }

      "text": "\n\nfunction _fzf_preview\n    set -l possible_command (string split ' ' $argv)\n    set -l command_size (count $possible_command)\n\n    if test $command_size -eq 1\n        __print_preview_cmd_1 $argv\n    else \n        if test $possible_command[1] = \"echo\"\n            __display_initial_param $argv\n            return\n        end\n        \n        if test $command_size -eq 2\n            __print_preview_cmd_2 $possible_command\n        else  \n            __print_preview_cmd_3 $possible_command\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n# __print_preview_cmd_1 - Prints the preview of the command\n# when the argument is of length 1.\n#\n# @param argv - $argv of size 1 (no command) passed to _fzf_preview. Example below.\n#                       $argv                            preview\n#                  ____________________________________________________\n#                       ~/.config/nvim/init.vim  |    bat ~/.config/nvim/init.vim\n#                       ~/.config/nvim/          |    ls ~/.config/nvim/\n#                       nvim                     |    man nvim\n#\nfunction __print_preview_cmd_1\n    if test -d $HOME/$argv\n        set -U EXA_COLORS (vivid generate exa_theme)\n        exa --icons $HOME/$argv\n    else if test -d $argv\n        set -U EXA_COLORS (vivid generate exa_theme)\n        exa --icons $argv\n    else if test -f $HOME/$argv\n        bat-fzf-helper $HOME/$argv\n    else if test -f $argv\n        bat-fzf-helper $argv\n    else if type -q $argv\n        if type -fq $argv\n            man -a $argv 2> /dev/null | sed '/troff.*$/d' | bat-fzf-helper\n            #man $argv | batcat | grep --invert-match \"troff\";\n        else \n            bat-fzf-helper (functions -D $argv 2> /dev/null)\n        end\n    else \n        set -l dir (dirname $argv)\n        if test -d .git\n            git show $argv;\n        else if test -d $dir/.git\n            git show $argv;\n        else if test -d $dir;\n            exa --icons $dir;\n        else if test -d $HOME/$dir\n            exa --icons $HOME/$dir;\n        else\n            spaced_print_seperator;\n            set_random_color; echo \"UNSURE OF $argv\";\n            spaced_print_seperator;\n            set_random_color; echo \"Potential commands:\";\n            set_random_color; type -pa $argv;\n            spaced_print_seperator;\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n# __print_preview_cmd_2 - Prints the preview of the command\n# when there is an argument included. History function of fzf\n# will show results for commands that are not just a single ft/dir/man page.\n#\n# @param argv - array of $argv initially passed to _fzf_preview. Example below.\n#               \n#     command in _fzf_preview     cd ~/.config\n#     argv index                  [1]  [2]\n#\nfunction __print_preview_cmd_2\n    set -l cmd $argv[1]\n    set -l arg (string replace -r \"[.]+/\" \"\" \"$argv[2]\")\n    if test -d $HOME/$arg; or test -d $arg\n        __print_preview_cmd_1 $arg;\n    else if test -f $HOME/$arg; or test -f $arg\n        __print_preview_cmd_1 $arg;\n    else \n        # check for cmd to be of some recognized type\n        # correlating to a file or directory\n        if test $cmd = \"cd\"\n            __find_from_home_directory 1 $arg\n        else if test $cmd = \"nvim\"\n            __find_from_home_directory 0 $arg\n        else \n            __display_initial_param $argv\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n# __print_preview_cmd_3 - Prints the preview of the command\n# when there is an argument included. History function of fzf\n# will show results for commands that are not just a single ft/dir/man page.\n#\n# @param argv - array of $argv initially passed to _fzf_preview. Example below.\n#               \n#     command in _fzf_preview     cd ~/.config\n#     argv index                  [1]  [2]\n#\nfunction __print_preview_cmd_3\n    __display_initial_param $argv\n    set -l cmd $argv[1]\n    set -l arg $argv[2]\n    set -l remaining $argv[3..]\n    print_seperator;\n    echo \"\"($cmd --help);\n    print_seperator;\n    set -l found_pipe false\n    for f_d in $remaining\n        if string match -qae -- \"echo\" \"$fd\"\n            set found_pipe false\n            continue;\n        else if string match -qae -- \"-\" \"$f_d\"\n            set found_pipe false\n            continue;\n        else if string match -qae -- \"|\" \"$f_d\"\n            set found_pipe true;\n            continue;\n        else if test $found_pipe \n            __print_preview_cmd_1 $f_d\n            set found_pipe false\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n\n# __find_from_home_directory - Finds the file or directory\n# from the home directory.\n#\n# @param is_dir - boolean value to determine if the file is a directory\n# @param name - the name of the file or directory\n#\nfunction __find_from_home_directory \n    set -l is_dir $argv[1]\n    set -l name $argv[2]\n    set -l found\n    echo \"$is_dir\"\n    if test $is_dir -eq 0\n        set found (fd -a --base-directory \"$HOME\" --type f --hidden --glob \"$name\")\n    else\n        set found (fd -a --base-directory \"$name\" --type d --hidden)\n    end\n    for item in $found\n        if test -d $item\n            lst $item\n        else\n            bat-fzf-helper $item;\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n# __display_initial_param - Prints the initial preview of the command\n#\n# @param argv - $argv passed to _fzf_preview. Example below.\n#\n#               _________________________\n#               $argv\n#               _________________________\n#\nfunction __display_initial_param\n    set_color normal; print_seperator;\n    set_random_color; echo \"$argv\"; \n    set_color normal; print_seperator;\nend\n"
    }

  "params": {
    "textDocument": {

      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-recent-dirs\n    set -l result (get_recent_dirs | __fzf_helper_cmd)\n    if test -n \"$result\"\n        if path resolve -q \"$result\"\n            cd $result\n        else\n            commandline -r \"$result\"\n            commandline -f repaint;\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n\nfunction __fzf_helper_cmd\n    set -l preview_cmd (string unescape  -- '--preview=\\'exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons ( path resolve {} ) \\'')\n    fzf --tiebreak=index \"$preview_cmd\" --preview-window \"right:60%:wrap\" \"$_FZF_NAV_KEYS\" \nend\n"
    }
  }
}

      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-recent-dirs\n    set -l result (get_recent_dirs | __fzf_helper_cmd | string trim --chars \\ )\n    if test -n \"$result\"\n        set new_result (string replace \"~\" $HOME $result)\n        if test -d $new_result; and test $new_result != $HOME\n            cd $new_result\n        else\n            commandline -r $result\n            commandline -f repaint;\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n\nfunction __fzf_helper_cmd\n    set preview_cmd (string unescape -- \"--preview='string replace \\\"~\\\" \\\"$HOME\\\" \\\"{}\\\" | read -l _p | exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons -x $_p'\")\n    fzf --ansi --filepath-word --tiebreak=index \"$preview_cmd\" --preview-window=right:30%:wrap \"$_FZF_NAV_KEYS\" \nend\n"
    }
  }
}

  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/fzf-recent-dirs.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-recent-dirs\n    set -l result (get_recent_dirs | __fzf_helper_cmd | string trim --chars \\ )\n    if test -n \"$result\"\n        set new_result (string replace \"~\" $HOME $result)\n        if test -d $new_result; and test $new_result != $HOME\n            cd $new_result\n        else\n            commandline -r $result\n            commandline -f repaint;\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n\nfunction __fzf_helper_cmd\n    #set preview_cmd (string unescape -- \"--preview='string replace \\\"~\\\" \\\"$HOME\\\" \\\"{}\\\" | read _p | exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons -x $_p'\")\n    fzf --ansi --filepath-word --tiebreak=index \"$_FZF_NAV_KEYS\" #$preview_cmd\" --preview-window=right:30%:wrap \" \nend\n"

onDefinition

scopes: 1
onReference
function fzf-dir-preview
    set -l dir (string replace -r --all '~' "$HOME" "$argv")
    exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons $dir 
    if test -d "$dir"
        exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons $dir
    else 
        error_text "EXA ERROR: "
        echo -n "'$dir'"
        error_text " is not a valid directory"
    end
end

function error_text
        set_color red --bold
        echo -n "$argv"
        set_color normal --background normal
end

[FishLsp.onDidOpenTextDocument()]
{
  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/get_recent_dirs.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function get_recent_dirs --description \"mru directories, or files recently used in the path argument\" --argument-names dir\n    if test -n \"$dir\"\n        # passing a path to this file, will find all recent subpaths in mru\n        $HOME/.config/fish/scripts/recent_dirs.ts \"$dir\"\n    else\n        # nothing passed to this file, outputs all recent dirs\n        $HOME/.config/fish/scripts/recent_dirs.ts \n    end\nend\n\n"
    }
  }
}

      "text": "function fzf-dir-preview\n    set -l dir (string replace -r --all '~' \"$HOME\" \"$argv\")\n    if test -d \"$dir\"\n        exa-tree \"$dir\"\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo -n \"'$dir'\"\n        error-text \" is not a valid directory\"\n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n"
    }
  }
}

      "text": "function fzf-dir-preview\n    set -l dir (string replace -r --all '~' \"$HOME\" \"$argv\")\n    if test -d \"$dir\"\n        echo \"RECENT FILES\"\n        get_recent_dirs \"$dir\" | exa-cmd \n        print_seperator_spaced\n        exa-cmd \"$dir\"\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo -n \"'$dir'\"\n        error-text \" is not a valid directory\"\n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n"
    }
  }

      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function get_recent_dirs --description \"mru directories, or files recently used in the path argument\" --argument-names dir\n    if test -n \"$dir\"\n        # passing a path to this file, will find all recent subpaths in mru\n        $HOME/.config/fish/scripts/recent_dirs.ts \"$dir\"\n    else\n        # nothing passed to this file, outputs all recent dirs\n        $HOME/.config/fish/scripts/recent_dirs.ts \n    end\nend\n\n"
    }
  }
}

{
  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/fzf-dir-preview.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-dir-preview\n    set -l dir (string replace -r --all '~' \"$HOME\" \"$argv\")\n    if test -d \"$dir\"\n        echo \"RECENT FILES IN $dir\"\n        show-recent-files \"$dir\"\n        print_seperator\n        exa-cmd \"$dir\"\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo -n \"'$dir'\"\n        error-text \" is not a valid directory\"\n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons --group-directories-first --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\nfunction show-recent-files --argument-names dir \n    set -l files (get_recent_dirs \"$dir\" | head -n 5)\n    set count 1\n    for file in $files\n        set -l pretty_file (exa $dir/$file --icons)\n        set -l icon (string split --max=1 ' ' $pretty_file)[1]\n        _number-text $count\n        _file-text $file\n        set count (math $count + 1)\n    end\nend\n\nfunction _file-text --argument-names file\n    set -l split_text (string split --max=1 '/' --right \"$file\")\n    if test (count split_text) -eq 2\n        set_color cyan --background normal\n        echo -n \"$split_text[1]\"\n        set_color blue --bold\n        echo \"$split_text[2]\"\n    else \n        set_color blue --bold\n        echo \"$file\"\n    end\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _number-text --argument-names num\n    set_color black --bold\n    echo -n \"  $num.) \"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n"
    }
  }
}

{
  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/fzf-dir-preview.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-dir-preview\n    set -l dir (string replace -r --all '~' \"$HOME\" \"$argv\")\n    if test -d \"$dir\"\n        echo \"RECENT FILES IN $dir\"\n        show-recent-files \"$dir\"\n        print_seperator\n        exa-cmd \"$dir\"\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo -n \"'$dir'\"\n        error-text \" is not a valid directory\"\n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons --group-directories-first --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\nfunction show-recent-files --argument-names dir \n    set -l files (get_recent_dirs \"$dir\" | head -n 5)\n    set count 1\n    for file in $files\n        _number-text $count\n        _icon-text $dir $file\n        _file-text $file\n        set count (math $count + 1)\n        set_color normal --background normal\n    end\nend\n\nfunction _file-text --argument-names file\n    set -l split_text (string split --no-empty \"/\" --max=1 --right \"$file\")\n    if test (count split_text) -ge 2\n        set fname $split_text[2]\n        set fpath $split_text[1]\n        set_color yellow\n        echo -n \"$fpath/\"\n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$path[2]\"\n    else \n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$file\"\n    end\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _number-text --argument-names num\n    set_color black --bold\n    echo -n \"  $num.) \"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _icon-text --argument-names dir file\n    printf \"%s\" (exa \"$dir/$file\" --icons | string split '/' --max=1 --fields=1)\n    echo -n \" \"\nend\n"
    }
  }
}

      "text": "function fzf-dir-preview\n    set -l dir (string replace -r --all '~' \"$HOME\" \"$argv\")\n    if test -d \"$dir\"\n        echo \"RECENT FILES IN $dir\"\n        show-recent-files \"$dir\"\n        print_seperator\n        exa-cmd \"$dir\"\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo -n \"'$dir'\"\n        error-text \" is not a valid directory\"\n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons --group-directories-first --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\nfunction show-recent-files --argument-names dir \n    set -l files (get_recent_dirs \"$dir\" | head -n 5)\n    set count 1\n    for file in $files\n        _number-text $count\n        _icon-text $dir $file\n        _file-text $file\n        set count (math $count + 1)\n        set_color normal --background normal\n    end\nend\n\nfunction _file-text --argument-names file\n    set -l split_text (string split --no-empty \"/\" --max=1 --right \"$file\")\n    if test (count split_text) -ge 1\n        set fname $split_text[2]\n        set fpath $split_text[1]\n        set_color yellow\n        echo -n \"$fpath/\"\n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$path[2]\"\n    else \n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$file\"\n    end\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _number-text --argument-names num\n    set_color black --bold\n    echo -n \"  $num.) \"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _icon-text --argument-names dir file\n    printf \"%s\" (exa $dir/$file --icons | string split '/' --max=1 --fields=1)\nend\n"
    }
  }
}

{
  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/fzf-dir-preview.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-dir-preview\n    set -l dir (string replace -r --all '~' \"$HOME\" \"$argv\")\n    if test -d \"$dir\"\n        echo \"RECENT FILES IN $dir\"\n        show-recent-files $dir \n        print_seperator\n        exa-cmd \"$dir\"\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo \"Can't find directory\"\n        echo -n \"Path: \" | lolcat -t\n        echo \"'$dir'\" \n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons --group-directories-first --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\nfunction show-recent-files --argument-names dir \n    set -l files (get_recent_dirs \"$dir\" | head -n 5)\n    set count 1\n    for file in $files\n        if not test -e \"$dir/$file\"\n            continue\n        end\n        _number-text $count\n        _icon-text $dir $file\n        _file-text $file\n        set count (math $count + 1)\n        set_color normal --background normal\n    end\nend\n\nfunction _file-text --argument-names file\n    if string match -rq '/' \"$file\";\n        set -l split_text (string split --no-empty \"/\" --max=1 --right \"$file\")\n        set fname $split_text[2]\n        set fpath $split_text[1]\n        set_color yellow\n        echo -n \"$fpath/\"\n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$fname\"\n    else \n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$file\"\n    end\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _number-text --argument-names num\n    set_color black --bold\n    echo -n \"  $num.) \"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _icon-text --argument-names dir file\n    printf \"%s\" (exa $dir/$file --icons | string split '/' --max=1 --fields=1)\nend\n"
    }
  }
}

  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/fzf-dir-preview.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-dir-preview\n    set -l dir (string replace -r --all '~' \"$HOME\" \"$argv\")\n    if test -d \"$dir\"\n        echo \"RECENT FILES IN $dir\"\n        show-recent-files $dir \n        print_seperator\n        exa-cmd \"$dir\"\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo \"Can't find directory\"\n        echo -n \"Path: \" | lolcat -t\n        echo \"'$dir'\" \n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons --group-directories-first --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\nfunction show-recent-files --argument-names dir \n    set -l files (get_recent_dirs \"$dir\" | head -n 5)\n    set count 1\n    for file in $files\n        if not test -e \"$dir/$file\"\n            continue\n        end\n        _number-text $count\n        _icon-text $dir $file\n        _file-text $file\n        set count (math $count + 1)\n        set_color normal --background normal\n    end\nend\n\nfunction _file-text --argument-names file\n    if string match -rq '/' \"$file\";\n        set -l split_text (string split --no-empty \"/\" --max=1 --right \"$file\")\n        set fname $split_text[2]\n        set fpath $split_text[1]\n        set_color yellow\n        echo -n \"$fpath/\"\n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$fname\"\n    else \n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$file\"\n    end\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _number-text --argument-names num\n    set_color black --bold\n    echo -n \"  $num.) \"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _icon-text --argument-names dir file\n    printf \"%s\" (exa $dir/$file --icons | string split '/' --max=1 --fields=1)\nend\n"
    }
  }
}

{
  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/fzf-dir-preview.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-dir-preview --argument-names pathname show_after\n    set -l dir (string replace -r --all '~' \"$HOME\" \"$pathname\")\n    if test -d \"$dir\"\n        echo \"RECENT FILES IN $dir\"\n        show-recent-files $dir \n        print_seperator;\n        exa-cmd \"$dir\";\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo \"Can't find directory\"\n        echo -n \"Path: \" | lolcat -t\n        echo \"'$dir'\" \n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --icons --group-directories-first --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\nfunction show-recent-files --argument-names dir \n    set -l files (get_recent_dirs \"$dir\" | head -n 5)\n    set count 1\n    for file in $files\n        if not test -e \"$dir/$file\"\n            continue\n        end\n        _number-text $count\n        _icon-text $dir $file\n        _file-text $file\n        set count (math $count + 1)\n        set_color normal --background normal\n    end\nend\n\nfunction _file-text --argument-names file\n    if string match -rq '/' \"$file\";\n        set -l split_text (string split --no-empty \"/\" --max=1 --right \"$file\")\n        set fname $split_text[2]\n        set fpath $split_text[1]\n        set_color yellow\n        echo -n \"$fpath/\"\n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$fname\"\n    else \n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$file\"\n    end\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _number-text --argument-names num\n    set_color black --bold\n    echo -n \"  $num.) \"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _icon-text --argument-names dir file\n    printf \"%s\" (exa $dir/$file --icons | string split '/' --max=1 --fields=1)\nend\n"
    }
  }
}

\"RECENT FILES IN $dir\"\n        show-recent-files $dir \n        print_seperator;\n        exa --icons --group-directories-first \"$dir\";\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo \"Can't find directory\"\n        echo -n \"Path: \" | lolcat -t\n        echo \"'$dir'\" \n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --icons --group-directories-first --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\nfunction show-recent-files --argument-names dir \n    set -l files (get_recent_dirs \"$dir\" | head -n 5)\n    set count 1\n    for file in $files\n        if not test -e \"$dir/$file\"\n            continue\n        end\n        _number-text $count\n        _icon-text $dir $file\n        _file-text $file\n        set count (math $count + 1)\n        set_color normal --background normal\n    end\nend\n\nfunction _file-text --argument-names file\n    if string match -rq '/' \"$file\";\n        set -l split_text (string split --no-empty \"/\" --max=1 --right \"$file\")\n        set fname $split_text[2]\n        set fpath $split_text[1]\n --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _number-text --argument-names num\n    set_color black --bold\n    echo -n \"  $num.) \"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _icon-text --argument-names dir file\n    printf \"%s\" (exa $dir/$file --icons | string split '/' --max=1 --fields=1)\nend\n"

      "text": "function fzf-recent-dirs\n    set -l result (get_recent_dirs | fzf --ansi --filepath-word --tiebreak=index \"$_FZF_NAV_KEYS\" --preview \"fzf-dir-preview {}\"  --preview-window 'bottom:40%')\n    if test -n \"$result\"\n        set new_result (string replace \"~\" $HOME $result)\n        if test -d $new_result; and test \"$new_result\" != \"$HOME\"\n            fzf-dir-preview \"$PWD\"\n            #commandline -f complete\n            commandline -f repaint\n        else\n            commandline -r $result\n            commandline -f repaint;\n        end\n    end\nend\n\n\nfunction __fzf_helper_cmd\n    #set preview_cmd (string unescape -- \"--preview='string replace \\\"~\\\" \\\"$HOME\\\" \\\"{}\\\" | read _p | exa --sort=changed --reverse --icons -x $_p'\")\nend\n"

      "version": 1,
      "text": "function fzf-dir-preview \n    set -l dir (string replace -ra  '~' \"$HOME\" \"$argv\")\n    if test -d \"$dir\" ;and test -n \"$argv\"\n        echo \"\";\n        echo \"RECENT FILES IN $dir\"\n        show-recent-files $dir \n        print_seperator;\n        exa --icons --group-directories-first \"$dir\";\n    else \n        error-text \"EXA ERROR: \"\n        echo \"Can't find directory\"\n        echo -n \"Path: \" | lolcat -t\n        echo \"'$dir'\" \n    end\nend\n\nfunction error-text\n    set_color red --bold\n    echo -n \"$argv\"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction exa-cmd --argument-names dir\n    exa --icons --group-directories-first --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\n# command to display directory contents in tree format, with the last used files at the top\nfunction exa-tree --argument-names dir \n    exa --tree --sort=changed --reverse --icons --git-ignore $dir\nend\n\nfunction show-recent-files --argument-names dir \n    set -l files (get_recent_dirs \"$dir\" | head -n 5)\n    set count 1\n    for file in $files\n        if not test -e \"$dir/$file\"\n            continue\n        end\n        _number-text $count\n        _icon-text $dir $file\n        _file-text $file\n        set count (math $count + 1)\n        set_color normal --background normal\n    end\nend\n\nfunction _file-text --argument-names file\n    if string match -rq '/' \"$file\";\n        set -l split_text (string split --no-empty \"/\" --max=1 --right \"$file\")\n        set fname $split_text[2]\n        set fpath $split_text[1]\n        set_color yellow\n        echo -n \"$fpath/\"\n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$fname\"\n    else \n        set_color blue\n        echo \"$file\"\n    end\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _number-text --argument-names num\n    set_color black --bold\n    echo -n \"  $num.) \"\n    set_color normal --background normal\nend\n\nfunction _icon-text --argument-names dir file\n    printf \"%s\" (exa $dir/$file --icons | string split '/' --max=1 --fields=1)\nend\n"
    }
  }
}

    }
  }
}

[onDidSaveTextDocument]: file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/test-fish-lsp.fish
onDefinition
lso
scopes: 1
# ls original version (ascii, system version)

function lso
    if test (count $argv) -eq 0
        /usr/bin/ls;
    else 
        /usr/bin/ls $argv;
    end
end


#complete -c lso --wraps ls

[FishLsp.onDidOpenTextDocument()]
{
  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/lso.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "# ls original version (ascii, system version)\n\nfunction lso\n    if test (count $argv) -eq 0\n        /usr/bin/ls;\n    else \n        /usr/bin/ls $argv;\n    end\nend\n\n\n#complete -c lso --wraps ls\n"
    }
  }
}

  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/test-fish-lsp.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "function test-fish-lsp --argument-names file --description \"Check a file for syntax errors\"\n    echo \"$file\"\n    lso\n    fzf-local-node_modules\n    __test_small\nend\n\n\n## this is a comment\nfunction __test_small \n    if string match --regex '^(\\w{10}).fish' -- \"$argv\"\n        echo \"matched\" | string pad -c ' ' \n    end\n    string match --regex '[[:alnum:]]' \"$argv\"\n\n    # padding a stirng\n    string pad --char \" \" $argv \n\n    set_color --background black white \n    set -l variable_name \"v\" \n    whatis -? --config-file --help --regex \"*\" \n\n    set -l variable_name (string split0 --fields 1 --right --max 4 '\\t' \"$argv\")\n    \n    string pad --width 10 --char \" \" \"$argv\" \n\n    set -l variable_name \"value\" \n\n\n    if test -n \"$variable_name\" \n        echo \"variable_name is not empty\" \n    end\n\n    for i in (seq 1 (count $variable_name))\n    end\n\n    for i in $variable_name\n        echo $i\n    end\n    set variable_name \"value\" \nend\n\n\nset -l file \"test.fish\"\ntest-fish-lsp $file\n"
    }
  }
}
[FishLsp.onDidOpenTextDocument()] uri: /home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/test-fish-lsp.fish
opened document: file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/test-fish-lsp.fish
analyzed document: file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/test-fish-lsp.fish
onReference
function test-fish-lsp --argument-names file --description "Check a file for syntax errors"
    echo "$file"
    lso
    fzf-local-node_modules
    __test_small
end


## this is a comment
function __test_small 
    if string match --regex '^(\w{10}).fish' -- "$argv"
        echo "matched" | string pad -c ' ' 
    end
    string match --regex '[[:alnum:]]' "$argv"

    # padding a stirng
    string pad --char " " $argv 

    set_color --background black white 
    set -l variable_name "v" 
    whatis -? --config-file --help --regex "*" 

    set -l variable_name (string split0 --fields 1 --right --max 4 '\t' "$argv")
    
    string pad --width 10 --char " " "$argv" 

    set -l variable_name "value" 


    if test -n "$variable_name" 
        echo "variable_name is not empty" 
    end

    for i in (seq 1 (count $variable_name))
    end

    for i in $variable_name
        echo $i
    end
    set variable_name "value" 
end


set -l file "test.fish"
test-fish-lsp $file

variable_name
onReference
function test-fish-lsp --argument-names file --description "Check a file for syntax errors"
    echo "$file"
    lso
    fzf-local-node_modules
    __test_small
end

## this is a comment
function __test_small 
    if string match --regex '^(\w{10}).fish' -- "$argv"
        echo "matched" | string pad -c ' ' 
    end
    string match --regex '[[:alnum:]]' "$argv"

    # padding a stirng
    string pad --char " " $argv 

    set_color --background black white 
    set -l variable_name "v" 
    whatis -? --config-file --help --regex "*" 

    set -l variable_name (string split0 --fields 1 --right --max 4 '\t' "$argv")
    
    string pad --width 10 --char " " "$argv" 

    set -l variable_name "value" 


    if test -n "$variable_name" 
        echo "variable_name is not empty" 
    end

    for i in (seq 1 (count $variable_name))
    end

    for i in $variable_name
        echo $i
    end
    set variable_name "value" 
end

function test-fish-lsp --argument-names file --description "Check a file for syntax errors"
    echo "$file"
    lso
    fzf-local-node_modules
    __test_small
end


## this is a comment
function __test_small 
    if string match --regex '^(\w{10}).fish' -- "$argv"
        echo "matched" | string pad -c ' ' 
    end
    string match --regex '[[:alnum:]]' "$argv"

    # padding a stirng
    string pad --char " " $argv 

    set_color --background black white 
    set -l variable_name "v" 
    whatis -? --config-file --help --regex "*" 

    set -l variable_name (string split0 --fields 1 --right --max 4 '\t' "$argv")
    
    string pad --width 10 --char " " "$argv" 

    set -l variable_name "value" 


    if test -n "$variable_name" 
        echo "variable_name is not empty" 
    end

    for i in (seq 1 (count $variable_name))
    end

    for i in $variable_name
        echo $i
    end
    set variable_name "value" 
end

test-fish-lsp $file

[FishLsp.onDidOpenTextDocument()] uri: /home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/toggle_prompt.fish
opened document: file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/toggle_prompt.fish
analyzed document: file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/toggle_prompt.fish
onDocumentSymbols
length: 13
onReference
# changes the size of the powerline prompt

function toggle_prompt -d "Toggle the size of the powerline prompt"
    touch $prompt_size_file;
    set -l file_found (cat -p $prompt_size_file)
    if test "$file_found" = ""
        echo "0" > $prompt_size_file;
    end
    if set -q argv;and test "$argv" = "-r";
        __reset_prompt_size_flag;
        return;
    end
    if test $file_found -eq 0
        echo "1" > $prompt_size_file;
        lengthen_prompt; commandline -f repaint;
        return;
    else if test $file_found -eq 1
        echo "0" > $prompt_size_file;
        shorten_prompt; commandline -f repaint;
        return;
    else 
        __debug_info_unseen_pflag;
    end
end

function __debug_info_unseen_pflag
    spaced_print_seperator;
    set_color red --bold;
    echo -n "Error:";
    reset_color;set_color brred --italic;
    echo " $prompt_size_file is not a valid value";
    echo "       this message also means that the no value";
    echo "       was read from the file in ~/.config/fish";
    spaced_print_seperator;
    cat $prompt_size_file;
    spaced_print_seperator;
    set_random_color --background;
    echo " USAGE: toggle_prompt [-r]";
    echo ""
    echo "        -r: reset the prompt size to the default";
    echo "";
    echo "        all other flags will print this message";
    echo "";
    echo "ideally toggle_prompt function should not take flags";
    print_seperator;
    set_random_color --underline --background;
    echo "Two files called from spaced_print_seperator.fish";
    echo ""
    set_random_color --background;
    echo -n "    [1] -"; set_random_color; echo " $HOME/.config/fish/functions/shorten_prompt.fish";
    echo ""
    set_random_color --background;
    echo -n "    [2] -"; set_random_color; echo " $HOME/.config/fish/functions/lengthen_prompt.fish";
    spaced_print_seperator;
    set_random_color --italic;
    echo "Now setting to default value of 0";
    echo ""
    set_random_color --italic;
    echo "this should never happen, but if it does you can reset"
    set_random_color;echo -n "file: ";
    set_random_color;echo "$prompt_size_file"
    echo "";
    spaced_print_seperator;
    echo 'Use Command: echo "0" > $prompt_size_file';
    spaced_print_seperator;
end

#function __help_print_helper
#    spaced_print_seperator
#    echo "toggle_prompt / toggle_prompt.fish"

#    echo "Toggle the size of the powerline prompt"

#    echo "Usage: toggle_prompt [h|help] [s|small] [l|large] [n|no-change]"
#    echo ""
#    echo "passing no flags will just directly toggle the prompt, where as flags will override this default behavior"
#    spaced_print_seperator;
#    echo "Options:"
#    echo "  [ f | first ]     - do not change the prompt from prev size "
#    echo "  [ n | no-change ] - do not change the prompt"
#    echo "  [ s | short ]     - make the prompt short"
#    echo "  [ l | long ]      - make the prompt large"
#    echo "  [ h | help ]      - Print this help message"
#    spaced_print_seperator;
#end

function __reset_prompt_size_flag
    echo "0" > $prompt_size_file;
    shorten_prompt; commandline -f repaint;
    spaced_print_seperator;
    echo "saw reset flag in toggle_prompt.fish";
    spaced_print_seperator;
    source_fish;and exec fish;
end




prompt_size_file

Provides the opposite functionality to toggle_prompt\"\n    touch $prompt_size_file;\n    set -l file_found (/usr/bin/cat $prompt_size_file)\n    if test \"$file_found\" = \"\"\n        echo \"0\" > $prompt_size_file;\n    end\n    if test $file_found -eq 0\n        shorten_prompt;\n        return;\n    else if test $file_found -eq 1\n        lengthen_prompt;\n        return;\n    end\nend\n\n"

onDocumentSymbols
length: 6
onDefinition
pushd_all_in_path
scopes: 1
# cdh and dirs are controlled by variables "$dirprev" and "$dirnext", and directly use
# variable "$dirstack" to store the stack of directories.
# $dirstack is an array where index 0 is the top of the stack.
function pushd_all_in_path
    set -l curr_dirs
    set -l dirpath_array (string split '/' --no-empty "$PWD" || echo '') # arrary of dirs in $PWD -> ["home", "user", "dir1", "dir2"] 
    for new_dir in $dirpath_array
        set --append  curr_dirs (string join '/' -- "$curr_dirs[-1]" "$new_dir")
        if not test -d "$curr_dirs[-1]"
            echo "[ERROR] pushd_all_in_path could not find '$existing_dir'"
            return 1
        end
    end
    if not test (count $dirpath_array) -eq 0
        set --prepend curr_dirs '/' # add root since path is correct
    end
    for existing_dir in $curr_dirs
        pushd "$existing_dir"
    end
    return 0
end

{
  "params": {
    "textDocument": {
      "uri": "file:///home/ndonfris/.config/fish/functions/pushd_all_in_path.fish",
      "languageId": "fish",
      "version": 1,
      "text": "# cdh and dirs are controlled by variables \"$dirprev\" and \"$dirnext\", and directly use\n# variable \"$dirstack\" to store the stack of directories.\n# $dirstack is an array where index 0 is the top of the stack.\nfunction pushd_all_in_path\n    set -l curr_dirs\n    set -l dirpath_array (string split '/' --no-empty \"$PWD\" || echo '') # arrary of dirs in $PWD -> [\"home\", \"user\", \"dir1\", \"dir2\"] \n    for new_dir in $dirpath_array\n        set --append  curr_dirs (string join '/' -- \"$curr_dirs[-1]\" \"$new_dir\")\n        if not test -d \"$curr_dirs[-1]\"\n            echo \"[ERROR] pushd_all_in_path could not find '$existing_dir'\"\n            return 1\n        end\n    end\n    if not test (count $dirpath_array) -eq 0\n        set --prepend curr_dirs '/' # add root since path is correct\n    end\n    for existing_dir in $curr_dirs\n        pushd \"$existing_dir\"\n    end\n    return 0\nend\n\n\n\n"
    }
  }
}
